Setup default printer for use by individual user:

Individual user can save a default setting that include the default
printer name and other settings to a template file.  This file
is located in the HOME directory of the user.  The file is called
".defplot.tem" for Composer and ".defLeplot.tem" for layout tools.

HOW TO SETUP PLOTTER TEMPLATE FILE:

If you want to customerize the your plotter setting, you can modify the
plotter setting in the plot submit/Option form, then click on "Save"
template to save the setting in you ~/.defplot.tem file.  Next time
when you start the system, your customerized template file will be loaded.
Same procedure to save the template to ~/.defLeplot.tem for layout tools.

To create a default plotter template file, In Composer, select
Design/Plot/Submit... menu, click on "Plot Options...", select your
default plotter name, and click "Fit to Page" button once.  Now, close
the dialog box by clicking OK.  In the "Submit Plot" dialog box, fill
in Template File as "~/.defplot.tem", and click "Save".  From now on,
when you invoke Composer, it will automatically load the template file
from your home directory ~/.defplot.tem and preset the plotter name and
other settings for you.  You can also repeat these
steps for layout tools, just change the Template File to "~/.defLeplot.tem".
